Rating: 4
After returning from New Year's in Key West I was looking for a 4Star dessert as an extra tip for our pet sitters. THIS IS IT. Importantly the lime juice and zest must be increased. For us doubling wasn't quite enough. Look at the juice-to-cream ratio in the KeyLimeMousse recipe on this site and/or taste the batter...the lime flavor will be milder in the chill dessert than it is in the batter. Also I cut the tiny limes in half and squeezed them with pliers. Trimming the fruit bits hanging out of the squeezed lime and adding it into the batter. I baked the crust for 10 min at 350 and doubled the gelatin to ensure the mousse was firm. [1 envelope gelatin= 1T so I used 2T.] The mousse was firm but not 'rubbery.' My only complaint: this dessert is straight calories! yet it tastes light, creamy, wonderful...

