Rating: 4
This dessert is a 10+. I made it for a wedding shower. It was one of the three I made for this event. I "iced" the cake in stabalized whipping cream. It was beautiful. It sat at room temperature (cool room) for about two hours. It was a little less "stable" than the other two desserts. I think I would add 1/2 pkg of gelatin and use cold water instead of the lime juice. Then I would heat the gelatin until melted. I would add the gelatin and lime juice to the melted chocolate. Better would be to "cook" the gelatin mixture with the heated cream but I don't know if it would work. So, the best thing would be to serve the cake when it is still very cool, so it is easy to serve and nice and firm. I would like to make this cake with a raspberry filling. My sister likes raspberry so she may try it. I would do this again for a shower. It's perfect.

